#   MEM tickets: memory-safety audit

Active tickets from the 2026-06-05 whole-codebase memory-safety audit; the full per-defect digest (severity, file, one-liner for all 45) lives in [MEM]. Each entry below is one open ticket — a landed one (verify with `be log | grep MEM-NNN`) drops off. The 10 below remain; the 6 JSC-blocked `js` defects (MEM-007/032/033/034/035/039) were dropped as stale — superseded by the landed JABC review (JS-002..014), with `js/convert.cpp` removed as dead code. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

##  Active tickets

 -  [MEM-010] — CURL unchecked alloc null-deref plus easy-handle and slist leaks (abc/CURL.c).
 -  [MEM-019] — graf `call()` early-return skips mmap/handle cleanup (graf/MERGE.c, MAP.c, LOG.c, REBASE.c).
 -  [MEM-021] — abc latent low-severity bounds/overflow hardening (SKIPfeed, MMAP resize, DNSNameText, utf8).
 -  [MEM-023] — tree-walk recursion holds a 1MB buffer per level with no depth cap (keeper/KEEP.c, WALK.c).
 -  [MEM-024] — push-side recursive walk holds a 1MB mmap per frame; errors swallowed (keeper/WIRECLI.c).
 -  [MEM-025] — `first_name` slice dangles into the compacted advert buffer (keeper/WIRECLI.c).
 -  [MEM-027] — `patch_walk` does unbounded BASS carving (~29MB/level), exhausting the arena (sniff/PATCH.c).
 -  [MEM-031] — WOOFApiOpen leaks dogs/buffers on a later open failure (woof/CONN.c).
 -  [MEM-041] — sniff error-path resource leaks in PATCH blob-write and POST commit.
 -  [MEM-042] — keeper REFSResolve leaks the ULOG map on a long URI; KEEPGetRemote double-error rarena leak.

